    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>July 13 article about technological advances in farming misstated some facts about Landsat satellites used for monitoring crop growth</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Circuits on July 13 about technological advances in farming misstated the altitude of Landsat satellites used to provide images of fields for monitoring crop growth. They are 437 miles above the earth, not 20,000 feet. The article also misstated the resolution of the images. Each pixel represents roughly 1,000 square yards, not 5 to 10 square yards.</p>
      </block>
